<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Jammu & Kashmir</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">Heaven on <em>Earth</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Jammu & Kashmir, often called Paradise on Earth, is a breathtaking region of unparalleled natural beauty, spiritual significance, and cultural diversity. Nestled in the Himalayas with snow-capped peaks, pristine valleys, serene lakes and lush gardens, Kashmir epitomizes alpine beauty. The region has a rich history spanning centuries with magnificent temples, shrines and heritage sites reflecting Hindu, Islamic, Buddhist and Sikh traditions. From the stunning Dal Lake in Srinagar with its iconic houseboats to the high-altitude Ladakh deserts, from the pilgrimage sites of Vaishno Devi and Amarnath to the adventure capital Gulmarg, Jammu & Kashmir offers experiences that touch the soul. A land of saints and scholars, warriors and poets, Jammu & Kashmir represents India's cultural synthesis and spiritual depth. Despite challenges, the region continues to enchant visitors with its magnificent landscapes, warm hospitality and timeless charm.</p>
</section>

<section id="weather" class="fade-in">
